definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-diphosphoglycerate + H2O -eq- 2-phospho-D-glycerate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-2-hydroxyglutarate + O2 -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + hydrogen peroxide.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of an aleurone grain.
The volume enclosed within the autophagic vacuole membrane.
A membrane-associated protein complex that is required for a late stage of endosomal transport. In budding yeast, this complex consists of Vps55p and Vps68p proteins.
The double lipid bilayer enclosing the etioplast and separating its contents from the rest of the cytoplasm -  includes the intermembrane space.
Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a etioplast and form the etioplast envelope.

label.value: monolayer-surrounded lipid storage body outer lipid monolayer

definition.value: The single layer of phopholipids surrounding a lipid storage body.
Catalysis of the reaction -  P1-P6-bis(5'-adenosyl) hexaphosphate + H2O -eq- AMP + adenosine 5'-pentaphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  P1-P6-bis(5'-adenosyl) pentaphosphate + H2O -eq- AMP + adenosine 5'-tetraphosphate.
Enables the directed movement of a glycoprotein, any protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

A vacuolar membrane-associated protein complex that is required for activation of microautophagy during exit from rapamycin-induced growth arrest. In budding yeast, S. cerevisiae, this complex includes Gtr1p, Gtr2p, Meh1p, and Slm4p.

Isoenergetic transfer of ubiquitin from one protein to an existing ubiquitin chain via the reaction X-ubiquitin + Y-ubiquitin --gt- Y-ubiquitin-ubiquitin + X, where both the X-ubiquitin and Y-ubiquitin-ubiquitin linkages are thioester bonds between the C-terminal glycine of ubiquitin and a sulfhydryl side group of a cysteine residue.
A small (70-100 nm) cytoplasmic granule that contains a number of centrosomal proteins -  centriolar satellites traffic toward microtubule minus ends and are enriched near the centrosome.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any part of a dynactin complex -  dynactin is a large protein complex that activates dynein-based motor activity.

A protein complex that forms a subcomplex of the 90S preribosome and is required for the subsequent assembly of the rest of the preribosome. In S. cerevisiae, it is composed of Utp5p, Utp4p, Nan1p, Utp8p, Utp9p, Utp10 and Utp15p.
A protein complex that forms a subcomplex of the 90S preribosome. In S. cerevisiae, it is composed of Rrp7p, Utp22p, Ckb1p, Cka1p, Ckb2p and Cka2p.
A protein complex that forms a subcomplex of the 90S preribosome. In S. cerevisiae, it is composed of Mpp10p, Imp3p and Imp4p.
Catalysis of the unwinding of an RNA helix in the direction 3' to 5'.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate -  this reaction drives the unwinding of an RNA helix in the direction 3' to 5'.
A protein complex that associates with the primary cilium and is involved in cilium biogenesis -  consists of seven conserved proteins -  BBS1, BBS2, BBS4, BBS5, BBS7, BBS8 and BBS9.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of a chromaffin granule.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of an esterosome.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of a glycosome.
The volume enclosed by any of the membranes of the thin, flattened cisternae that form the central portion of the Golgi complex.
Any process that results in the conversion of one or more primary non-coding RNA (ncRNA) transcripts into one or more mature ncRNA molecules.
Any process involved in forming the mature 5' end of a non-coding RNA molecule.
Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of an snRNA molecule.
Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U1 snRNA molecule.
Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U2 snRNA molecule.
Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U4 snRNA molecule.
Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U5 snRNA molecule.
Any process involved in forming the mature 3' end of a U6 snRNA molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a phosphatidylglycerol + H2O -eq- 1,2-diacylglycerol + glycerol 3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphatidylcholine + H2O -eq- 1,2-diacylglycerol + a choline phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + chondroitin -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + chondroitin sulfate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + chondroitin -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + chondroitin 2'-O-sulfate. Results in sulfation of glucuronic acid and iduronic acid residues.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + heparan sulfate -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + sulfated heparan sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate + H2O -eq- phosphatidylinositol-3,4-bisphosphate + phosphate.
The volume enclosed by the hydrogenosome membrane.
The volume enclosed by the melanosome membrane.
The volume enclosed by the microneme membrane.
The volume enclosed by the protein storage vacuole membrane.
The innermost portion of the centromeric region of a chromosome, encompassing the core region of a chromosome centromere and the proteins that bind to it.
The portion of the centromeric region of a chromosome that flanks the core region, encompassing repeated regions of a chromosome centromere and the proteins that bind to it.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with U3 small nucleolar RNA.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with box C|D small nucleolar RNA.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with box H|ACA small nucleolar RNA.
A multisubunit proteasome complex that localizes in the cytoplasm as dot-like structures when cells are in a quiescent state.
Any protein complex that binds to a specialized RNA cap structure at any time in the lifetime of the RNA.
